title: Election of the Speaker of the House
new-page: true
tags: event
view-if: speaker_election_needed = 1 and rep_majority = 1
on-arrival: speaker_election_needed = 0;

= Election of the Speaker

With our majority in the House of Representatives, we must choose a Speaker to preside over the chamber. The Speaker sets the legislative agenda, assigns committee chairmanships. This is not a ceremonial choice.

[? if speaker != "" : The current Speaker is [+ speaker +]. ?]

- @Colfax
- @Stevens
- @Blaine
- @Dawes
- @Garfield
- @Washburne
- @keep_speaker: Keep the current Speaker.
- @dem_speaker_note

@Colfax
title: Schuyler Colfax (Indiana)
subtitle: [? if speaker = "Colfax" : Currently serving: retain him ?][? if speaker != "Colfax" : Moderate Republican. Affable, well-liked across factions. ?]
view-if: year <= 1869
on-arrival: {!
    let wasSpeaker = (Q.speaker === "Colfax");
    Q.speaker = "Colfax";
    Q.speaker_party = "R";

    if (!wasSpeaker) {
        Q.moderate_strength += 4;
        Q.moderate_dissent -= 3;
        Q.radical_dissent += 2;
        Q.conservative_dissent -= 2;
        Q.liberal_dissent -= 2;
        Q.middle_class_rep += 2;
    } else {
        Q.moderate_dissent -= 2;
        Q.conservative_dissent -= 1;
    }

    Q.speaker_boosted_committee = "fiscal_policy";
    Q.speaker_boost_amount = 2;
!}
go-to: speaker_end

Schuyler Colfax, the "Smiler," is elected Speaker. Known for his warm personality and skill at building consensus, he is popular across the party's moderate and conservative wings. Radicals tolerate him, if not love him.

[? if speaker = "Colfax" : Colfax continues his tenure. The House settles into its familiar rhythms under his steady hand. ?]

His speakership opens channels to Ways & Means, strengthening our hand on tariff legislation.

@Stevens
title: Thaddeus Stevens (Pennsylvania)
subtitle: [? if speaker = "Stevens" : Currently serving ?][? if speaker != "Stevens" : Radical choice. Transforms the speakership into a weapon for Reconstruction. ?]
view-if: year <= 1868 and stevens_advisor = 1
on-arrival: {!
    Q.speaker = "Stevens";
    Q.speaker_party = "R";

    Q.moderate_dissent += 5;
    Q.conservative_dissent += 8;
    Q.radical_strength += 8;
    Q.radical_dissent -= 6;
    Q.liberal_dissent += 4;

    Q.freemen_rep += 4;
    Q.rural_dem -= 2;

    // Stevens drives impeachment hard
    Q.impeachment_unlocked = 1;

    Q.speaker_boosted_committee = "civil_rights";
    Q.speaker_boost_amount = 3;
!}
go-to: speaker_end

Thaddeus Stevens storms into the Speaker's chair like a force of nature. His iron control of the House floor and committee assignments transforms the chamber into an engine of Radical Reconstruction. Democrats are apoplectic. Conservative Republicans are alarmed. Radicals are finally satisfied.

His dual role as Speaker and party advisor means he cannot devote his full attention to either — his advisor actions will come more slowly.

[? if impeachment_unlocked = 1 : Stevens, as Speaker, will drive the impeachment process with particular ferocity. ?]


@Blaine
title: James Blaine (Maine)
subtitle: [? if speaker = "Blaine" : Currently serving ?][? if speaker != "Blaine" : Ambitious moderate. Strong legislator, eye on the presidency. ?]
view-if: year >= 1868
on-arrival: {!
    let wasSpeaker = (Q.speaker === "Blaine");
    Q.speaker = "Blaine";
    Q.speaker_party = "R";

    if (!wasSpeaker) {
        Q.moderate_strength += 5;
        Q.conservative_strength += 3;
        Q.radical_dissent += 4;
        Q.liberal_dissent -= 2;
        Q.middle_class_rep += 3;
    }

    Q.speaker_boosted_committee = "fiscal_policy";
    Q.speaker_boost_amount = 2;
!}
go-to: speaker_end

James Blaine of Maine takes the gavel. Energetic, politically cunning, and already cultivating a national profile, Blaine is a skilled legislative operator. He consolidates support from the moderate and conservative wings and proves adept at managing the floor.

His ambitions, however, extend beyond the speakership. Keep an eye on him.


@Dawes
title: Henry Dawes (Massachusetts)
subtitle: Fiscal conservative, known for probity and reform sympathies.
view-if: year >= 1867
on-arrival: {!
    Q.speaker = "Dawes";
    Q.speaker_party = "R";

    Q.conservative_strength += 5;
    Q.conservative_dissent -= 4;
    Q.radical_dissent += 5;
    Q.liberal_dissent -= 3;
    Q.moderate_dissent += 2;

    Q.middle_class_rep += 4;
    Q.workers_rep -= 2;

    Q.speaker_boosted_committee = "monetary_policy";
    Q.speaker_boost_amount = 2;
!}
go-to: speaker_end

Henry Dawes brings a reputation for financial integrity and reform sympathies to the speakership. His selection satisfies the conservative and liberal factions, who see him as a counterweight to Radical excess.

Radicals distrust him. The working class, sensing he will not be their champion, shift slightly.

His speakership strengthens fiscal oversight and accelerates currency legislation.


@Garfield
title: James A. Garfield (Ohio)
subtitle: Rising star. War hero, moderate Radical, skilled debater.
view-if: year >= 1869
on-arrival: {!
    Q.speaker = "Garfield";
    Q.speaker_party = "R";

    Q.moderate_strength += 4;
    Q.radical_dissent -= 2;
    Q.conservative_dissent += 1;
    Q.liberal_dissent -= 1;

    Q.workers_rep += 2;
    Q.rural_rep += 2;
    Q.freemen_rep += 2;

    Q.speaker_boosted_committee = "civil_rights";
    Q.speaker_boost_amount = 2;
!}
go-to: speaker_end

James Garfield, the self-made man from Ohio and celebrated Union general, brings credibility with both Radical and moderate wings. A gifted orator, he commands the floor with natural authority.

His broad appeal reduces factional friction and opens up Reconstruction-minded legislation.


@Washburne
title: Elihu Washburne (Illinois)
subtitle: Grant ally. Reliably loyal, limited ambition, strong in foreign affairs.
view-if: year >= 1866 and year <= 1872
on-arrival: {!
    Q.speaker = "Washburne";
    Q.speaker_party = "R";

    Q.moderate_strength += 3;
    Q.conservative_strength += 2;
    Q.radical_dissent += 1;
    Q.liberal_dissent += 2;

    Q.europe_relation += 2;

    Q.speaker_boosted_committee = "judiciary";
    Q.speaker_boost_amount = 2;
!}
go-to: speaker_end

Elihu Washburne, Grant's close political ally from Illinois, takes the gavel. Reliable, unflashy, and content to serve the party rather than himself, he keeps the caucus orderly and the Grant White House happy.

His deep interest in foreign affairs — he will later serve as minister to France — opens new diplomatic avenues.


@keep_speaker
title: Retain [+ speaker +] as Speaker.
view-if: speaker != "" and rep_majority >= 2
on-arrival: moderate_dissent -= 1; conservative_dissent -= 1
go-to: speaker_end

The House re-elects [+ speaker +] without controversy. Continuity has its value.

@dem_speaker_note
title: (Democrats hold the House we cannot elect a Speaker.)
view-if: rep_majority = 0
go-to: dem_speaker

@dem_speaker
on-arrival: {!
    // Michael Kerr (1875) or Samuel Randall (1876)
    if (Q.year >= 1875) {
        Q.speaker = "Randall";
        Q.speaker_party = "D";
    } else {
        Q.speaker = "Kerr";
        Q.speaker_party = "D";
    }

    Q.radical_dissent += 5;
    Q.moderate_dissent += 3;
    Q.reconstruction_support -= 5;

    Q.speaker_boosted_committee = "";
    Q.speaker_boost_amount = 0;
!}
go-to: speaker_end

With the Democrats in control of the House, [+ speaker +] takes the gavel as Speaker. Our legislative agenda is now effectively blocked. Bills that reach the floor will be shaped by Democratic priorities, not ours.

This is the consequence of losing the House. Reconstruction stalls. Our chairmanships are stripped. We can oppose, but we cannot govern.


@speaker_end
title: Finish Voting
on-arrival: speaker_election_needed = 0

The election of [+ speaker +] as Speaker is complete.

[? if speaker_boosted_committee = "fiscal_policy" : The new Speaker's allies on Ways & Means will smooth the path for fiscal and tariff legislation. ?]
[? if speaker_boosted_committee = "monetary_policy" : The new Speaker prioritizes currency and banking legislation, speeding it through committee. ?]
[? if speaker_boosted_committee = "civil_rights" : The new Speaker assigns a Reconstruction Committee favorable to our agenda, speeding civil rights legislation through the House. ?]
[? if speaker_boosted_committee = "judiciary" : The new Speaker keeps pressure on the courts, speeding judiciary reform through committee. ?]
[? if speaker_boosted_committee = "" : With Democrats controlling the chamber, no committee favors our agenda. ?]